<p class=mibilllongbillnumber>HOUSE BILL NO. 4546</p>

<p class=mibilldonotdelete><img width=624 height=250
src="HB4546_files/image001.png"
alt="May 11, 2023, Introduced by Reps. Jaime Greene, St. Germaine, Schmaltz, Wendzel, Aragona, Meerman, Alexander, Bierlein, DeBoyer, Maddock, Johnsen, Markkanen, Cavitt, Hoadley, Outman, Rigas, Fox, Schriver, Wozniak, Bezotte, Martin, Neyer, Kunse, Friske, DeBoer, Carra, Schuette, Smit and Beeler and referred to the Committee on Government Operations."></p>

<p class=mibilltitle>A bill to require awards, rankings, and records of
outcomes in separate female and male sporting events to be categorized
consistent with each competitor's biological sex.</p>

<p class=mibillenactment>the people of the state of michigan enact:</p>

<p class=mibillstatute><a name="sec_import_start_1_1"></a>Sec. 1. This act may
be cited as the &quot;female athletics integrity of records (FAIR) act&quot;.</p>

<p class=mibillstatute><a name="sec_import_start_2_2"></a>Sec. 2. As used in
this act:</p>

<p class=mibillstatute>(a) <span style='color:black'>&quot;Biological sex&quot;
</span>means the state of being female or the state of being male, as an
innate, objective<span style='color:black'> </span>biological condition
determined at the conception of the human being.</p>

<p class=mibillstatute>(b) &quot;Sporting event&quot; means an athletic event to
which all of the following apply:</p>

<p class=mibillstatute>(<i><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>i</span></i>)
Individuals compete individually.</p>

<p class=mibillstatute>(<i><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>ii</span></i>)
There are separate competitions for females and males.</p>

<p class=mibillstatute>(<i><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>iii</span></i>)
The event is in whole or in part publicly funded.</p>

<p class=mibillstatute><a name="sec_import_start_3_3"></a>Sec. 3. Though an
individual in a sporting event participates in the competition designated for
members of the opposite <span style='color:black'>biological </span>sex,
official awards, rankings, and records of results shall nonetheless be
categorized consistent with each competitor's <span style='color:black'>biological
</span>sex.</p>

